monkey /ˈmʌŋkɪ/

(monkeys) 

1. N-COUNT A monkey is an animal with a long tail which lives in hot countries and climbs trees. 猴子 

2. N-COUNT If you refer to a child as a monkey , you are saying in an affectionate way that he or she is very lively and naughty. 淘气鬼 [情感] 

例： She's such a little monkey. 她是这么个小淘气。

